syscfg NEWS


2026-03-21 - 2026-03-29
=======================
* syscfg will trap EXIT instead of continuing to emulate it. (670ec0b)

* syscfg now has a standard cmdline and documentation. Additionally, it now
  builds shell-glossary into itself. (c205fcc)
  Breaking (backward-incompatible) change.

* Internally, the hint system underwent peculiar maintainer-focused
  improvements. (37d6931, 4ed6cc2, 89dcc88)

* The created filesystem parents for a write now inherit all relevant inode
  properties of the target, and their mode is additionally specified to be
  "umask-explicit" (default mkdir-driven directory mode).

* Synced shell-glossary to release 20260328. (de12818)

* A <newline> character (one) will always be stripped from the CRC hint when
  passed along with the string.

* EUID 0 is not a runtime requirement anymore. Instead, EACCES would be issued
  where appropriate.

* Fixed an oversight of how `-d`/`-D` options shall work and clarified their
  role and related documentation. Behavior now matches `-no-avoid`/`-no-sync`
  hints, respectively.
  Breaking (backward-incompatible) change.

* $opd has been renamed to $CLIENT_NAME and formally specified. Clients
  shall not set it themselves anymore; `syscfg` manages it now, and the caller
  can also specify it using `-n`/`--client-name`. Additionally, `syscfg` now
  supports passing any arguments to only one client and in turn does not
  consider the arguments to be more clients to execute.
  Breaking (backward-incompatible) change.


2026-03-13 - 2026-03-15
=======================
* Fixed a fatal missing log error scenario. (d16537e)

* Fixed file mode equivalence assert not working. (9da5d0a)

* Implemented inode synchronization for writes to avoid certain scenarios where
  a write is necessary (due to the state of the object on the filesystem) but
  nothing is being performed. (959b348)

* Logging (using the command API) for inode synchronization operations.

* Synced shell-glossary to release 20251116. (a08e5a3)


2025-09-27 - 2025-09-27
=======================
* Introduced hint_act(): A simple, pluggable hint outcome override mechanism.
  By default, it is implementation-defined (up to syscfg to utilize it).


2025-09-26 - 2025-09-26
=======================
* Hint `-clear-log` has been removed. The write API now supports `-trunc`
  to mean the same thing.
  Breaking (backward-incompatible) change.

* Hint `-log-fed` has been removed. The write API now supports `-color`
  to imply the same logic.
  Breaking (backward-incompatible) change.

* Hint `-out-req` has been renamed to `-req-out`.
  Breaking (backward-incompatible) change.

* __write() (the write API of syscfg) now supports hint `-sanit`.
  For more information, refer to the commit data.

* syscfg no longer provides $logf, $tmpd, and $tmpf. Clients are expected to
  manage temporary files on their own. To aid in this task, __ed() is ready to
  generate the file path specified by `-log` on its own, and the write API is
  ready to perform cleanup on it, given the hint `-sanit`.
  Breaking (backward-incompatible) change.


2025-09-25 - 2025-09-25
=======================
* Rework of __fed(); renamed to __ed().
  For more information, refer to the commit data.
  Breaking (backward-incompatible) change.


2025-09-23 - 2025-09-23
=======================
* Rework of the command execution API.
  For more information, refer to the commit data.
  Breaking change; existing code requires adjustment.


2025-09-15 - 2025-09-17
=======================
* Major rewrite of the writing API (i.e. most of syscfg).
  For more information, refer to the commit data.
  Breaking change; existing code requires adjustment.

* Introduced a basic __action() implementation to act as a replacement for
  __loc_delete() and __loc_empty().

* Renamed _err() to __err().
  Breaking change; existing code requires adjustment.

* Renamed _info() to __info().
  Breaking change; existing code requires adjustment.

* __action() takes no parameters anymore and instead uses $OBJ_PATH.
  Breaking change; existing code requires adjustment.

* __action() will now additionally preserve $OBJ alongside $OBJ_PATH, if
  defined and `-no-sanit` hint is given.

* Removed __git_get().
  Breaking change; existing code requires adjustment.


2025-09-05 - 2025-09-08
=======================
* Improved the handling in regards to dangling (broken) symbolic links.

* Renamed __OBJ_cmd() to __cmd_OBJ().
  Breaking change; existing code requires adjustment.

* Renamed interactive mode cmdline switch from `IE` to `I`.


2025-08-18 - 2025-09-02
=======================
* `shell-glossary`[1] is now a submodule and its functions are being sourced.

* FILE_preload() and __FILE_PATH_preload() have been removed.

* FILE(), FILE_PATH(), FILE_PATH_TARGET(), and FILE_octal() have been removed,
  __FILE_cmd() renamed, and the core file-related variables' names changed.
  For more information, refer to the commit data.
  Breaking change; existing code requires adjustment.

[1] https://github.com/mscalindt/shell-glossary


2025-08-17 - 2025-08-17
=======================
* Created tag `pre-split`.

* History starts anew, as syscfg is now general-purpose software not locked
  to a certain configuration.


2025-07-16 - 2025-08-08
=======================
* EXIT signal is now completely in-house simulated, enhancing portability.

* __FILE_cmd() now supports extended behavior, using an option block.
  Breaking change; existing code requires adjustment.

* Switched from BSD 2-Clause "Simplified" License to KEYCLA 1.0[1][2].

[1] https://github.com/mscalindt/keycla-license
[2] https://gitlab.com/mscalindt/keycla-license


2025-07-06 - 2025-07-10
=======================
* __git_get() now supports local repositories with first priority.
  Breaking change; existing code requires adjustment.

* Simplified log handling and removed its API.
  Breaking change; existing code requires adjustment.

* libfile() of syscfg has been replaced with the powerful fed() + libfile()
  combo from `shell-glossary`.
  Breaking change; existing code requires adjustment.

* __fed() now supports CRC32 verification for the format string.
  Breaking change; existing code requires adjustment.

* Optimized the handling of octal streams and clarified usage.
  Breaking change; existing code requires adjustment.

* $LF has been deprecated and removed.


2025-05-24 - 2025-06-19
=======================
* The client's name is now set and locked in a variable for the executed
  client to use.

* For regular files, the overwrite operation now deletes and creates
  the file instead of doing an in-place (we call it 'soft'[1])
  overwrite.

[1] 47cf24bcec4c


2025-05-06 - 2025-05-09
=======================
* Client output is separated from syscfg's output. More details here[1].

* Standardized error codes. More details here[2].

* Added __cmd() and __FILE_cmd() for centralized command execution.

* Clients are now launched in a subshell. More details here[3].

[1] d366385243ec
[2] e69ae2b2b3b5
[3] 9b51b665cbcb


2025-04-22 - 2025-04-25
=======================
* Now exits with EPERM if not executed with root privileges.
  More details here[1].

* Separated the log file from the client's temporary file.

[1] 2df3e7114c43


2025-04-16
==========
* Added `CREDITS` and `DEPENDENCIES` files.

* Moved `syscfg` to src/ (`src/syscfg`).

* Created tag `250`, tagging 250 commits before major refactor.


2023-01-22
==========
* Added software configuration stages to allow for immediate
  reconfiguration.


2022-12-26
==========
* Initial commit.


